LTG H.R. McMaster delivered a speech at the U.S.-Baltic Centennial Summit, congratulating Estonia, Latvia, and Lithuania on their 100th Anniversary of Independence. He discussed the ongoing contest between free and open societies and closed and repressive systems, highlighting Russia's aggression and attempts to undermine sovereignty and stability. McMaster emphasized the need for confidence, action, cooperation, and competition in defending freedom and countering Russian aggression. He also called for investment in cyber infrastructure, increased defense spending by NATO countries, and the preservation of strategic confidence in order to ensure the triumph of free societies.